As of the [[2010 United States census|2010 census]], there were 5,437 people, 2,330 Households, and 1,417 families residing in the borough. The racial makeup of the borough was 94.5% White, 2.1% Hispanic or Latino ancestry of any race, 2.5% Black or African American, 0.9% Asian, 1.3% were two or more races, 0.4% were some other race and 0.2% Native American.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.census.gov|title = Schuylkill Haven, Pennsylvania|website = [[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date = 23 January 2020}}</ref> As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], the borough's population was 5,253.

